<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/382: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>)<note n="95" xml:id="d346fn95">Repeated to the Minister in Nicaragua as
                                    telegram No. 78.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-04T17:00:00-04:00">August 4, 1930—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>39. Legation’s 69, August 1, 4 p.m. The Department perceives no
                                objection to your submitting to the Honduran Government for approval
                                the changes in the boundary protocol suggested by the Nicaraguan
                                Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>